Characteristics[SpikedCompound]: 13 non-mouse proteins
the iRT kit provided by Biognosys
Characteristics[CleavageAgent]: digestion was carried out using trypsin (Serva, Heidelberg, Germany) at an enzyme to substrate ratio of approx. 1:27 at 37 °C overnight
Characteristics[ReductionReagent]: reduction with dithiothreitol (DTT, final concentration of 5 mm) for 20 min at 56 °C
Characteristics[AlkylationReagent]: alkylated with iodoacetamide (13.75 mm final concentration) at ambient temperature for 30 min in the dark
Characteristics[NumberOfSamples]: The GS consisted of five different samples
Characteristics[NumberOfTechnicalReplica: each sample was measured in triplicate in DDA and DIA mode using the same instrumental setup (nano-LC coupled to Q-Exactive HF)
Comment[Instrument]: transferred into a Q Exactive HF mass spectrometer (Thermo Fisher Scientific).
nano-LC coupled to Q-Exactive HF
Comment[Separation]: For LC separation the nanoHPLC system Ultimate 3000 (Thermo Fisher Scientific) was used with a PepMap 100 C18 (100 μm ID × 2 cm, particle size 5 μm, pore size 100 Å; Thermo Fisher Scientific) as precolumn and a PepMap C18 (75 μm × 50 cm, particle size 2 μm, pore size 100 Å; Thermo Fisher Scientific) as analytical column.
Comment[GradientTime]: Peptides were separated by a 120 min gradient using 0.1% formic acid (FA) as buffer A and 84% ACN in 0.1% FA as buffer B.
Comment[MS2MassAnalyzer]: Fragment analysis (MS2) was subdivided into 22 DIA isolation windows of equal width (49 m/z wide) using a resolution of 30,000 at 200 m/z (AGC 3 × 106, auto maximum injection time).
Comment[CollisionEnergy]: Stepped collision energy was used (25.5%, 27 and 30% NCE).
